# Content Rules

This project is a personal engineering blog at sujeet.pro. When working with content files, follow these guidelines.

## Guidelines

Read the full guidelines before creating or editing content:

- `ai-guidelines/content-structure.md` — Content types, frontmatter, layout rules, citations
- `ai-guidelines/markdown.md` — Markdown features and syntax
- `ai-guidelines/diagrams.md` — Diagram authoring with diagramkit
- `ai-guidelines/packages.md` — @pagesmith/core and diagramkit reference

## Quick Reference

### Frontmatter (required for all content)

```yaml
---
title: "Title"
description: "One-line description"
publishedDate: 2026-03-15
lastUpdatedOn: 2026-03-20
tags: [topic-a, topic-b]
---
```

Do NOT set `layout` or `category` — resolved from `meta.json5`.

### Content Types

- Articles: `content/articles/<slug>/README.md` — deep-dive, citations required
- Blogs: `content/blogs/<slug>/README.md` — shorter, personal
- Projects: `content/projects/<slug>/README.md` — technical descriptions

### Diagrams

Write source files (`.mermaid`, `.excalidraw`, `.drawio`, `.dot`) in `<slug>/diagrams/`. Never generate SVG directly. Run `npm run diagrams` to render.

Reference with:

```html
<picture>
  <source media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)" srcset="./diagrams/name-dark.svg" />
  <img src="./diagrams/name-light.svg" alt="Description" />
</picture>
```

### Validation

```bash
npm run validate         # Check frontmatter
npm run build            # Full build verification
vp check                 # Format + lint
```
